This paper discusses the impact of older scholarly articles, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The sub-category of Digital Libraries (cs.DL) is the most likely fit as it deals with the organization and retrieval of scholarly articles. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is also a likely fit as it deals with the search and retrieval of information. Cybernetics (cs.CY) deals with the study of communication and control in systems, which could be relevant to the analysis of citation networks. Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) could also be relevant as it deals with the analysis of networks and their impact. Finally, Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) could be relevant as it deals with the analysis of the impact of older cryptographic algorithms.
